<td colspan="2" style="text-align: center; font-size: 90%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa; line-height: 1.5em;"><a href="/wiki/File:November_1951_nuclear_test_at_Nevada_Test_Site.jpg" class="image" title="November 1951 nuclear test at Nevada Test Site.jpg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ca/November_1951_nuclear_test_at_Nevada_Test_Site.jpg/300px-November_1951_nuclear_test_at_Nevada_Test_Site.jpg" width="300" height="240" border="0" /></a><br />
November 1951 nuclear test at Nevada Test Site. Test is shot "Dog" from <a href="/wiki/Operation_Buster-Jangle" title="Operation Buster-Jangle">Operation Buster</a>, with a yield of 21 kilotons. It was the first U.S. nuclear field exercise conducted on land; troops shown are a mere 6&#160;miles (9.7&#160;km) from the blast.</td>
